{{DISPLAYTITLE:''Star Wars'': Force for Change}} {{Infobox organization | name = ''Star Wars'': Force for Change | image = File:Star_Wars_Force_for_Change_Logo.svg | named_after = ''[[Star Wars]]'' | formation = {{start date and age|2014}} | founder = | founding_location = | type = | tax_id = <!-- or | vat_id = (for European organizations) --> | registration_id = <!-- for non-profit org --> | purpose = Expanding [[Science, technology, engineering, and mathematics|STEM]] education | headquarters = [[Los Angeles]] | key_people = [[Mark Hamill]], [[Daisy Ridley]] | parent_organization = [[Lucasfilm]], [[Disney]] | affiliations = [[FIRST]], [[UNICEF]] | website = {{URL|https://www.starwars.com/force-for-change}} }} '''''Star Wars'': Force for Change''' is a ''[[Star Wars]]''-themed charity program run by [[Lucasfilm]] and [[The Walt Disney Company]] that collects donations to fund solutions for global problems.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.unicefusa.org/donate/be-force-change/23586 |title=Tax-Deductible Donations Save Children's Lives |work=[[UNICEF]] USA |access-date=18 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160530102034/https://www.unicefusa.org/donate/be-force-change/23586 |archive-date=30 May 2016}}</ref> The organization also sells ''Star Wars''-themed merchandise using the profits for charitable causes.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://charity.ebay.com/forceforchange/ |title=Star Wars: Force for Change |work=[[Ebay.com]] |access-date=18 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160514125512/http://charity.ebay.com/forceforchange/ |archive-date=14 May 2016}}</ref>
==History== Launched in 2014, the program worked closely with [[UNICEF]] by selling sweepstakes for the seventh ''Star Wars'' film of the saga ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' and raised approximately $4.2&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thewaltdisneycompany.com/star-wars-inspiring-change-around-the-world/|title=Star Wars: Inspiring Change Around the World|work=The Walt Disney Company}}</ref>
===2015 campaigns=== In addition to its recent campaigns was selling lucky draws to people who could make [[cameo appearance]]s in ''The Force Awakens'',<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/voluntary-sector-network/2015/dec/16/organisation-helping-star-wars-become-force-for-change |title=How my organization is helping Star Wars become a force for change |newspaper=[[the Guardian]] |first=Ryan |last=Cummins |date=16 December 2015 |access-date=18 August 2019 |publisher=[[Guardian News & Media Limited]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.omaze.com/experiences/starwars-episode-vii |title=CLOSED: You Could Be in Star Wars: Episode VII |work=[[Omaze]].com |access-date=18 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160807013855/https://www.omaze.com/experiences/starwars-episode-vii |archive-date=17 August 2016 |date=17 October 2014 }}</ref> some of the actors from the films such as [[Mark Hamill]] visited Los Angeles Children's Hospital,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://zap2it.com/2015/12/star-wars-mark-hamill-darth-vader-childrens-hospital-force-for-change/ |title='Star Wars': Mark Hamill and Darth Vader visit Children's Hospital |work=[[Zap2It]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160421165223/http://zap2it.com/2015/12/star-wars-mark-hamill-darth-vader-childrens-hospital-force-for-change/ |archive-date=21 April 2016 |first=Aaron |last=Pruner |date=16 December 2015 |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref> while [[Harrison Ford]] appeared in a charity video to surprise fans.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/11/19/harrison-ford-force-change-charity-video |title=Harrison Ford surprises Star Wars fans in new Force For Change charity video |magazine=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |first=Anthony |last=Breznican |date=19 November 2015 |access-date=18 August 2019 |publisher=[[Meredith Corporation]]}}</ref>
===Fortieth anniversary announcement=== To commemorate the fortieth anniversary of the ''Star Wars'' franchise, organization members Mark Hamill and [[Daisy Ridley]] appeared on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' announcing to fans that they could help ''Star Wars'': Force for Change through UNICEF by going to Omaze and donating money to help children all over the world.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2017/04/11/star-wars-force-change-good-morning-america-featuring-mark-hamill-daisy-ridley/ |title=Star Wars Force For Change On Good Morning America, Featuring Mark Hamill And Daisy Ridley. |first=Veronica |last=Webb |work=[[Bleeding Cool]] |date=11 April 2017 |access-date=18 August 2019}}</ref>
===Collaboration with FIRST=== In 2019, Force for Change announced that they were working with [[FIRST]], a organizer of grade school robotics competitions, on FIRST's 2020 season. Due to this, the season was officially named FIRST RISE 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://info.firstinspires.org/first-rise-2020|title=FIRST RISE 2020|last=FIRST|website=info.firstinspires.org|language=en|access-date=2019-05-31}}</ref>
