'''''Yoda purpurata''''' is a species of [[acorn worm]] discovered 2,5km (about 1.5 miles) below the surface of the Atlantic ocean, and the sole species of the genus ''Yoda''. Ranging from {{convert|12|to|19|cm|in|abbr=on}} in length, it was named after the fictional character [[Yoda]] from the ''[[Star Wars]]'' franchise.<ref name="OAP">[http://www.ouramazingplanet.com/3592-new-worm-named-after-yoda.html Newly Discovered Acorn Worm Named After Yoda], retrieved 2012-10-06 18:05 UTC</ref><ref name="PriedeOsborn2012">{{cite journal|last1=Priede|first1=Imants G.|last2=Osborn|first2=Karen J.|last3=Gebruk|first3=Andrey V.|last4=Jones|first4=Dan|last5=Shale|first5=David|last6=Rogacheva|first6=Antonina|last7=Holland|first7=Nicholas D.|title=Observations on torquaratorid acorn worms (Hemichordata, Enteropneusta) from the North Atlantic with descriptions of a new genus and three new species|journal=Invertebrate Biology|volume=131|issue=3|year=2012|pages=244–257|issn=1077-8306|doi=10.1111/j.1744-7410.2012.00266.x|url=https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/34434/Priedeetal2012pdf.pdf;https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/34434/Priedeetal2012pdf.pdf}}</ref> It is the only known [[Hermaphrodite|hermaphroditic]] member within the phylum.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1111/j.1744-7410.2012.00266.x | volume=131 | issue=3 | title=Observations on torquaratorid acorn worms (Hemichordata, Enteropneusta) from the North Atlantic with descriptions of a new genus and three new species | year=2012 | journal=Invertebrate Biology | pages=244–257 | last1 = Priede | first1 = Imants G.| url=https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/34434/Priedeetal2012pdf.pdf;https://repository.si.edu/bitstream/handle/10088/34434/Priedeetal2012pdf.pdf }}</ref>

